headline: Southwest WiFi Upgrade And Board Changes Test Valuation And Momentum
summary: Southwest Airlines, NYSE:LUV, plans a fleetwide upgrade to Starlink satellite WiFi, targeting more than 300 aircraft by the end of 2026. The airline intends to offer high speed inflight internet access at no extra cost to loyalty program members. Two board directors have submitted resignations, leading to a reduction in board size and a reshaped governance structure. headline: As blizzard slams US Northeast, airlines report major disruptions
summary: A historic blizzard is slamming the US Northeast, accumulating a foot and a half of snow overnight from Sunday to Monday in New York City and across most of New Jersey, as the snow continues to fall. Morning Brief Host Julie Hyman reports remotely on the major disruptions reported by airlines today due to these weather conditions. To watch more expert insights and analysis on the latest market action, check out more Morning Brief.
